{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"siteUrl":"https://docs.vwa.la","title":"vwa.la help","description":"Everything you need to know about the vwa.la influencer marketing platform."}},"ghostPost":{"title":"Flickr","slug":"flickr","featured":false,"feature_image":"https://docs.ghost.io/content/images/2018/09/flickr.png","created_at_pretty":"20 September, 2018","published_at_pretty":"20 September, 2018","updated_at_pretty":"19 November, 2018","created_at":"2018-09-20T19:01:33.000+00:00","published_at":"2018-09-20T19:01:47.000+00:00","updated_at":"2018-11-19T09:48:33.000+00:00","excerpt":"All content from Flickr works with Ghost automatically via our OEmbed\nintegration. All you have to do is paste a URL!\n\nIf you're already sharing photos on Flickr [https://flickr.com]  then you'll\nprobably want a way to embed those images on your Ghost site. Using a robust\nexternal photo storage service is a great way to manage a large photo library\nand maintain optimum performance. Here's a quick guide for how to make things\nwork: \n\nCopy the URL of the photo\nGrab the URL of the photo you'd like ","meta_title":null,"meta_description":"All content from Flickr integrates with Ghost automatically using a sensible OEmbed integration. Grab a URL and add beautiful images to your site ðŸ‘‰","og_description":null,"og_image":null,"og_title":null,"twitter_description":null,"twitter_image":null,"twitter_title":null,"authors":[{"name":"John O'Nolan","slug":"john","bio":null,"profile_image":"//www.gravatar.com/avatar/f95828f4e92f1befebabfb7f65cdc8f2?s=250&d=mm&r=x","twitter":null,"facebook":null,"website":null}],"primary_author":{"name":"John O'Nolan","slug":"john","bio":null,"profile_image":"//www.gravatar.com/avatar/f95828f4e92f1befebabfb7f65cdc8f2?s=250&d=mm&r=x","twitter":null,"facebook":null,"website":null},"primary_tag":{"name":"Social","slug":"social","description":null,"feature_image":null,"meta_description":null,"meta_title":null,"visibility":"public"},"tags":[{"name":"Social","slug":"social","description":null,"feature_image":null,"meta_description":null,"meta_title":null,"visibility":"public"},{"name":"Content","slug":"content","description":null,"feature_image":null,"meta_description":null,"meta_title":null,"visibility":"public"},{"name":"#integration","slug":"hash-integration","description":null,"feature_image":null,"meta_description":null,"meta_title":null,"visibility":"internal"}],"plaintext":"All content from Flickr works with Ghost automatically via our OEmbed\nintegration. All you have to do is paste a URL!\n\nIf you're already sharing photos on Flickr [https://flickr.com]  then you'll\nprobably want a way to embed those images on your Ghost site. Using a robust\nexternal photo storage service is a great way to manage a large photo library\nand maintain optimum performance. Here's a quick guide for how to make things\nwork: \n\nCopy the URL of the photo\nGrab the URL of the photo you'd like to embed into your post or page\n\nPaste it into the Ghost editor\nWhen you paste it into the Ghost editor it'll be automatically transformed into\na rich embed of the photo you selected\n\nPublish your post\nThat's all there is to it! Ghost interacts with Flickr via their OEmbed\n[https://oembed.com/]  API in order to retrieve all the correct settings\nautomatically and serve your photo in the best way possible.\n\nHere's an example of the end result:\n\n[https://www.flickr.com/photos/johnonolan/26091690611/]Do more with Zapier\nAs always, you can power up your site even further using Zapier\n[https://zapier.com].  If you're already using Flickr for photos, then you might\nalso like some of these complimentary automations:","html":"<p>All content from Flickr works with Ghost automatically via our OEmbed integration. All you have to do is paste a URL!</p><p>If you're already sharing photos on <a href=\"https://flickr.com\">Flickr</a> then you'll probably want a way to embed those images on your Ghost site. Using a robust external photo storage service is a great way to manage a large photo library and maintain optimum performance. Here's a quick guide for how to make things work: </p><h2 id=\"copy-the-url-of-the-photo\">Copy the URL of the photo</h2><p>Grab the URL of the photo you'd like to embed into your post or page</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://docs.ghost.io/content/images/2018/11/image-31.png\" class=\"kg-image\"></figure><h2 id=\"paste-it-into-the-ghost-editor\">Paste it into the Ghost editor</h2><p>When you paste it into the Ghost editor it'll be automatically transformed into a rich embed of the photo you selected</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://docs.ghost.io/content/images/2018/11/image-17.png\" class=\"kg-image\"></figure><h2 id=\"publish-your-post\">Publish your post</h2><p>That's all there is to it! Ghost interacts with Flickr via their <a href=\"https://oembed.com/\">OEmbed</a> API in order to retrieve all the correct settings automatically and serve your photo in the best way possible.</p><p>Here's an example of the end result:</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-embed-card\"><a data-flickr-embed=\"true\" href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/johnonolan/26091690611/\" title=\"Venice Beach by JohnONolan, on Flickr\"><img src=\"https://farm2.staticflickr.com/1493/26091690611_849cbd83b8_b.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" alt=\"Venice Beach\"></a><script async src=\"https://embedr.flickr.com/assets/client-code.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script></figure><h2 id=\"do-more-with-zapier\">Do more with Zapier</h2><p>As always, you can power up your site even further using <a href=\"https://zapier.com\">Zapier</a><a>.</a> If you're already using Flickr for photos, then you might also like some of these complimentary automations:</p><div id=\"zap\" class=\"zapier\">\n    <script src=\"https://zapier.com/apps/embed/widget.js?services=flickr&limit=5&html_id=zap\"></script>\n</div>","custom_template":null,"url":"https://docs.ghost.io/flickr/","uuid":"3264